<div class="hero-unit">
  <h1>Weed.tw</h1>
  <p>Weed.tw is a tool to weed out the weeds from your twitter timeline.</p>
  <p><a href="/login" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Login with your Twitter account &raquo;</a></p>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="span4">
    <h3>Weed out the weeds</h3>
    <p>Weed.tw allows you to unfollow in bulk. If your timeline is getting out of hand this tool is for you. </p>
  </div>
  <div class="span4">
    <h3>Find new flowers to follow</h3>
    <p>This might be taking the metaphor too far, but when you are done weeding, weed.tw has a built in search to help you find new people to follow. </p>
  </div>
  <div class="span4">
    <h3>We store nothing</h3>
    <p>We do not have a database and will not store any personal information. All data needed for the authentication against twitter is stored in your web browser and will be removed when you restart your web browser.</p>
  </div>
</div>
